{
  "name": "analytics-nightly",
  "active": false,
  "notes": "NIGHTLY ANALYTICS COLLECTION — runs at 2:00 AM daily\n\nPURPOSE\nPulls engagement metrics from all platform APIs for published content and stores them in the platform_analytics Supabase table. Also checks monthly AI cost budget and sends Slack alert if over $15.\n\nSETUP GUIDE\n\n1. HOW TO IMPORT\n   n8n Settings → Workflows → Import → paste this JSON\n\n2. CREDENTIALS TO CONFIGURE\n   - Supabase API: Name it exactly 'Supabase Content Engine'\n   - Google Sheets OAuth2: Name it exactly 'Google Sheets Content Bank'\n   - Meta Graph API: Name it exactly 'Meta Graph API' (used for Instagram + Threads)\n   - YouTube Data API: Name it exactly 'YouTube Data API' (OAuth2, requires published channel)\n   - Slack API: Name it exactly 'Slack Content Pipeline' (for budget alerts to #content-pipeline)\n\n3. GOOGLE SHEETS SETUP\n   Create an 'Analytics' tab in the same Content Bank Google Sheet.\n   Columns in order: Date | Topic | Brand | Platform | Views | Likes | Comments | Shares | Reach\n   Update the Google Sheets node documentId with your Sheet ID.\n\n4. HOW TO ACTIVATE\n   Only activate AFTER:\n   - First content is published via the platform-publishers/ workflows\n   - platform_analytics table exists in Supabase (run 003_analytics.sql migration)\n   - All 5 credentials above are configured in n8n\n   Toggle workflow to Active to start nightly collection at 2 AM.\n\n5. TWITTER ANALYTICS LIMITATION (IMPORTANT)\n   Twitter/X free API tier does NOT include read access for tweet metrics.\n   The POST /2/tweets endpoint works on free tier for publishing.\n   GET endpoints for engagement data (views, likes, impressions) require the Basic tier ($100/month).\n   This contradicts the Phase 10 zero-subscriptions goal.\n   DECISION: Twitter metrics are logged as placeholder rows with raw_response = {\"error\": \"free_tier_no_read_access\"}.\n   Twitter analytics will remain at 0 until one of these conditions is met:\n   a) X restores free read access to the API\n   b) A free scraping solution is validated (e.g., nitter instance, Twitterpic)\n   c) Business growth justifies the $100/month Basic tier upgrade\n   Track engagement manually via Twitter Analytics dashboard in the meantime.\n\n6. SUBSTACK NOTE METRICS\n   Substack has no public API for Note engagement metrics (views, likes, restacks).\n   Notes are excluded from nightly analytics. Review manually at notes.sameerrijhsinghani.com.\n\n7. PLATFORM_ANALYTICS TABLE\n   Upsert pattern: ON CONFLICT (content_bank_id, platform, metric_date) DO UPDATE\n   This means running the workflow twice on the same day is safe — it overwrites with latest values.\n",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "nightly-cron",
      "name": "Nightly Cron: 2:00 AM Daily",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [160, 300],
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "cronExpression",
              "expression": "0 2 * * *"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "notes": "Fires at 2:00 AM every day. Low-traffic window reduces rate limit risk on platform APIs."
    },
    {
      "id": "get-published-content",
      "name": "Get Published Content from Supabase",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.supabase",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [380, 300],
      "credentials": {
        "supabaseApi": {
          "id": "SUPABASE_CRED_ID_PLACEHOLDER",
          "name": "Supabase Content Engine"
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "getAll",
        "table": "content_bank",
        "filterType": "string",
        "filterString": "status=eq.published",
        "options": {
          "limit": 500
        }
      },
      "notes": "Fetches all content_bank rows with status='published'. visual_assets JSONB contains platform post IDs: {youtube_video_id, instagram_post_id, threads_post_id, twitter_tweet_id, substack_url}."
    },
    {
      "id": "split-by-platform",
      "name": "Split by Platform",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.splitInBatches",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [600, 300],
      "parameters": {
        "batchSize": 1,
        "options": {}
      },
      "notes": "Process one content item at a time to avoid API rate limits. Each item fans out to platform branches below."
    },
    {
      "id": "branch-youtube",
      "name": "Branch: YouTube — Has video ID?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [820, 100],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            {
              "value1": "={{ $json.visual_assets?.youtube_video_id }}",
              "operation": "isNotEmpty"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "notes": "Only collect YouTube metrics if visual_assets.youtube_video_id is set."
    },
    {
      "id": "youtube-metrics-api",
      "name": "YouTube: GET Video Statistics",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [1040, 60],
      "parameters": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "https://www.googleapis.com/youtube/v3/videos",
        "authentication": "predefinedCredentialType",
        "nodeCredentialType": "youTubeOAuth2Api",
        "sendQuery": true,
        "queryParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "part",
              "value": "statistics,contentDetails"
            },
            {
              "name": "id",
              "value": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.visual_assets.youtube_video_id }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "response": {
            "response": {
              "responseFormat": "json"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "notes": "YouTube Data API v3 — returns viewCount, likeCount, commentCount, favoriteCount. Free quota: 10,000 units/day. This request costs 1 unit."
    },
    {
      "id": "youtube-upsert-analytics",
      "name": "YouTube: Upsert platform_analytics",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.supabase",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1260, 60],
      "credentials": {
        "supabaseApi": {
          "id": "SUPABASE_CRED_ID_PLACEHOLDER",
          "name": "Supabase Content Engine"
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "upsert",
        "table": "platform_analytics",
        "conflictColumns": "content_bank_id,platform,metric_date",
        "fieldsUi": {
          "fieldValues": [
            {
              "fieldId": "content_bank_id",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.id }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "platform",
              "fieldValue": "youtube"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "post_id",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.visual_assets.youtube_video_id }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "metric_date",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $today.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd') }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "views",
              "fieldValue": "={{ parseInt($json.items?.[0]?.statistics?.viewCount || '0') }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "likes",
              "fieldValue": "={{ parseInt($json.items?.[0]?.statistics?.likeCount || '0') }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "comments",
              "fieldValue": "={{ parseInt($json.items?.[0]?.statistics?.commentCount || '0') }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "brand",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.brand }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "raw_response",
              "fieldValue": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "notes": "Upserts YouTube metrics into platform_analytics. ON CONFLICT (content_bank_id, platform, metric_date) updates existing row — safe to run multiple times per day."
    },
    {
      "id": "branch-instagram",
      "name": "Branch: Instagram — Has post ID?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [820, 260],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            {
              "value1": "={{ $json.visual_assets?.instagram_post_id }}",
              "operation": "isNotEmpty"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "notes": "Only collect Instagram metrics if visual_assets.instagram_post_id is set."
    },
    {
      "id": "instagram-metrics-api",
      "name": "Instagram: GET Post Insights",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [1040, 220],
      "credentials": {
        "supabaseApi": {
          "id": "META_GRAPH_API_CRED_ID_PLACEHOLDER",
          "name": "Meta Graph API"
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "=https://graph.facebook.com/v22.0/{{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.visual_assets.instagram_post_id }}/insights",
        "sendQuery": true,
        "queryParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "metric",
              "value": "plays,likes,comments,reach,saved,impressions"
            },
            {
              "name": "access_token",
              "value": "={{ $credential.accessToken }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "response": {
            "response": {
              "responseFormat": "json"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "notes": "Meta Graph API: GET /{media-id}/insights. Returns plays (views for Reels), likes, comments, reach, saved, impressions. Requires instagram_business_account and media_insights permission."
    },
    {
      "id": "instagram-upsert-analytics",
      "name": "Instagram: Upsert platform_analytics",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.supabase",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1260, 220],
      "credentials": {
        "supabaseApi": {
          "id": "SUPABASE_CRED_ID_PLACEHOLDER",
          "name": "Supabase Content Engine"
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "upsert",
        "table": "platform_analytics",
        "conflictColumns": "content_bank_id,platform,metric_date",
        "fieldsUi": {
          "fieldValues": [
            {
              "fieldId": "content_bank_id",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.id }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "platform",
              "fieldValue": "instagram"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "post_id",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.visual_assets.instagram_post_id }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "metric_date",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $today.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd') }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "views",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $json.data?.find(m => m.name === 'plays')?.values?.[0]?.value || 0 }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "likes",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $json.data?.find(m => m.name === 'likes')?.values?.[0]?.value || 0 }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "comments",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $json.data?.find(m => m.name === 'comments')?.values?.[0]?.value || 0 }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "reach",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $json.data?.find(m => m.name === 'reach')?.values?.[0]?.value || 0 }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "saves",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $json.data?.find(m => m.name === 'saved')?.values?.[0]?.value || 0 }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "impressions",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $json.data?.find(m => m.name === 'impressions')?.values?.[0]?.value || 0 }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "brand",
              "fieldValue": "={{ $('Get Published Content from Supabase').item.json.brand }}"
            },
            {
              "fieldId": "raw_response",
              "fieldValue": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "branch-threads",
      "name": "Branch: Threads — Has post ID?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [820, 420],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            {
